The paper discusses the use of surrogate models and multi-objective evolutionary algorithms for automatic game balancing, which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of simulation-based objectives, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and simulation and modeling (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the approach to real-time strategy games, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
